  heroImg={heroImg}
  overviewTitle="The most powerful smile transformation available."
  overviewText="Porcelain veneers are ultra-thin ceramic shells — typically 0.3–0.5mm — bonded permanently to the front surface of your teeth. Each veneer is custom-designed to your facial proportions, giving you complete control over the color, shape, and length of your smile. The porcelain reflects light the same way natural enamel does, which is why expertly placed veneers are indistinguishable from real teeth."
  overviewExtra="Patients from Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck regularly choose Thrive Dental for porcelain veneers because of our smile design process. Before a single tooth is prepared, we use digital smile design software to map your facial proportions and build a virtual preview of your new smile — so you approve the result before we begin. For patients in Northern Queens looking for porcelain veneers without the Manhattan price tag, our Bayside practice offers the same caliber of cosmetic work in a neighborhood setting. Whether you're fixing one chipped tooth or transforming your entire smile, our cosmetic team has the artistry and clinical precision to deliver results that look completely natural."
