    },
    {
      number: '02',
      title: 'Tooth Preparation',
      desc: 'A thin layer of enamel (0.3–0.5mm) is gently removed from the front of each tooth to make room for the veneer. Local anesthesia ensures you feel nothing. Temporary veneers are placed the same day.',
    },
    {
      number: '03',
      title: 'Lab Fabrication',
      desc: 'Your digital impressions are sent to our ceramist lab, where each veneer is individually crafted from high-strength porcelain. This typically takes 2–3 weeks.',
