    {
      number: '04',
      title: 'Bonding & Final Fitting',
      desc: 'The permanent veneers are tried in, adjusted for color and fit, then bonded with a high-strength dental adhesive. We check your bite and make final refinements — you leave with your finished smile.',
    },
  ]}
  faq={[
    {
      q: 'How many veneers do I need?',
      a: 'It depends on your goals. Some patients treat a single chipped tooth with one veneer; others transform their entire visible smile with 6–10 veneers. We\'ll show you a digital smile preview before committing to any treatment so you can see and approve the result in advance.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Are veneers permanent? Do I have to shave down my teeth?',
      a: 'Veneers are considered a permanent treatment because a small amount of enamel (typically 0.3–0.5mm) must be removed to make room for the veneer. This means your teeth will always need to be covered once the process begins. The amount removed is minimal — far less than a crown requires.',
    },
    {
      q: 'How long do porcelain veneers last?',
      a: 'With proper care, high-quality porcelain veneers last 15–20 years. Avoid biting nails, chewing ice, or using teeth as tools. A nightguard is recommended if you grind your teeth. Regular checkups help us monitor the veneers and address any issues early.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Can veneers fix crooked teeth?',
      a: 'Veneers can create the appearance of straighter teeth by adjusting the shape and alignment of individual teeth. However, they work best for mild irregularities. For significant crowding or bite issues, Invisalign® may be a better starting point — or a combination of both.',
    },
    {
      q: 'How much do porcelain veneers cost in Bayside, NY?',
